{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848541736,"sessionID":"ses_2872e22efffe0q11C7PEsCSYsr","part":{"id":"prt_d78d249b1001T8G7uDtm9iv3t9","messageID":"msg_d78d23ec3001otOSZJqj047xfG","sessionID":"ses_2872e22efffe0q11C7PEsCSYsr","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_cd23d8cba3ce4bff8f0127df","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Design: AR-009 Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document describes the technical implementation for the Router module (`pkg/router`) that acts as an HTTP reverse proxy, routing incoming requests to appropriate AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter backends based on Kubernetes CRD resources.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Component Structure\n10: \n11: ```\n12: pkg/router/\n13: ├── router.go                   # Main router implementation\n14: ├── router_test.go             # Unit tests\n15: ├── handler.go                 # HTTP handler for proxy requests\n16: ├── handler_test.go            # Handler tests\n17: ├── resolver.go                # Route resolution logic\n18: ├── resolver_test.go           # Resolver tests\n19: ├── health.go                  # Health check manager\n20: ├── health_test.go             # Health check tests\n21: ├── config.go                  # Configuration structures\n22: └── types.go                   # Type definitions\n23: ```\n24: \n25: ### Integration Points\n26: \n27: - **Clientset**: Uses generated `versioned.Clientset` for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n28: - **Informers**: Watches `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` resources via `SharedInformerFactory`\n29: - **Listers**: Provides cached read access for route resolution\n30: - **HTTP Client**: Reusable connection pool for backend requests\n31: \n32: ### High-Level Flow\n33: \n34: ```\n35: ┌─────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n36: │   Client    │────▶│   Handler    │────▶│  Resolver   │────▶│  RouteEntry     │\n37: │             │     │              │     │             │     │  (from routes)  │\n38: └─────────────┘     └──────────────┘     └─────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n39:                            │                                          │\n40:                            ▼                                          ▼\n41:                     ┌──────────────┐                          ┌─────────────────┐\n42:                     │   Router     │                          │  Backend URL    │\n43:                     │  (manages    │                          │  (proxy target) │\n44:                     │   routes)    │                          │                 │\n45:                     └──────────────┘                          └─────────────────┘\n46:                            │\n47:                            ▼\n48:                     ┌──────────────┐\n49:                     │  Informers   │\n50:                     │  (watch CRs) │\n51:                     └──────────────┘\n52: ```\n53: \n54: ## Data Structures\n55: \n56: ### Router\n57: \n58: ```go\n59: type Router struct {\n60:     config          *RouterConfig\n61:     routes          sync.Map // map[string]*RouteEntry\n62:     httpClient      *http.Client\n63:     kubeClient      *versioned.Clientset\n64:     informerFactory informers.SharedInformerFactory\n65:     runtimeInformer v1alpha1.AgentRuntimeInformer\n66:     interpreterInformer v1alpha1.CodeInterpreterInformer\n67:     stopCh          chan struct{}\n68:     wg              sync.WaitGroup\n69:     mu              sync.RWMutex\n70: }\n71: ```\n72: \n73: ### RouterConfig\n74: \n75: ```go\n76: type RouterConfig struct {\n77:     KubeConfig          *rest.Config\n78:     ListenAddr          string\n79:     ReadTimeout         time.Duration\n80:     WriteTimeout        time.Duration\n81:     IdleTimeout         time.Duration\n82:     MaxConnsPerHost     int\n83:     HealthCheckInterval time.Duration\n84:     HealthCheckTimeout  time.Duration\n85:     UnhealthyThreshold  int\n86:     Namespace           string // empty means all namespaces\n87: }\n88: ```\n89: \n90: ### RouteEntry\n91: \n92: ```go\n93: type RouteEntry struct {\n94:     Name       string\n95:     Namespace  string\n96:     Kind       string // \"AgentRuntime\" or \"CodeInterpreter\"\n97:     BackendURL string\n98:     Health     HealthStatus\n99:     UpdatedAt  time.Time\n100: }\n101: ```\n102: \n103: ### HealthStatus\n104: \n105: ```go\n106: type HealthStatus struct {\n107:     Healthy             bool\n108:     LastCheck           time.Time\n109:     Error               error\n110:     ConsecutiveFailures int\n111:     mu                  sync.Mutex\n112: }\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ### RouteKey\n116: \n117: ```go\n118: // routeKey generates unique key for route storage\n119: func routeKey(namespace, kind, name string) string {\n120:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s/%s\", namespace, kind, name)\n121: }\n122: ```\n123: \n124: ## API Contracts\n125: \n126: ### Incoming Request Format\n127: \n128: **Path Pattern:**\n129: ```\n130: /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/{resourceType}/{name}[/{subpath}]\n131: ```\n132: \n133: **Resource Types:**\n134: - `agentruntimes` → Maps to AgentRuntime CR\n135: - `codeinterpreters` → Maps to CodeInterpreter CR\n136: \n137: **Headers (added by router):**\n138: - `X-Forwarded-For`: Client IP\n139: - `X-Real-IP`: Client IP\n140: - `X-Forwarded-Host`: Original host\n141: - `X-Forwarded-Proto`: Request scheme\n142: \n143: ### Processor Interface\n144: \n145: ```go\n146: type RouterInterface interface {\n147:     Start(ctx context.Context) error\n148:     Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n149:     ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request)\n150: }\n151: ```\n152: \n153: ### Resolve Operation\n154: \n155: **Input**: `*http.Request`\n156: \n157: **Output**: `*RouteEntry` or error\n158: \n159: **Behavior**:\n160: 1. Parse namespace, resourceType, name from path\n161: 2. Look up route from `routes` sync.Map\n162: 3. Check backend health status\n163: 4. Return RouteEntry or error\n164: \n165: ### Proxy Operation\n166: \n167: **Input**: `http.ResponseWriter`, `*http.Request`, `*RouteEntry`\n168: \n169: **Output**: error\n170: \n171: **Behavior**:\n172: 1. Build backend URL from RouteEntry.BackendURL\n173: 2. Clone request with new context\n174: 3. Add forwarding headers\n175: 4. Execute request via `httpClient.Do()`\n176: 5. Copy response headers and body\n177: 6. Handle errors appropriately\n178: \n179: ## Error Handling\n180: \n181: ### Error Types\n182: \n183: ```go\n184: var (\n185:     ErrRouteNotFound      = errors.New(\"route not found\")\n186:     ErrNoHealthyBackends  = errors.New(\"no healthy backends available\")\n187:     ErrInvalidResourceType = errors.New(\"invalid resource type\")\n188:     ErrMalformedPath      = errors.New(\"malformed request path\")\n189: )\n190: \n191: var (\n192:     ErrBackendConnection  = errors.New(\"failed to connect to backend\")\n193:     ErrBackendTimeout     = errors.New(\"backend timeout\")\n194:     ErrBackendUnavailable = errors.New(\"backend unavailable\")\n195: )\n196: ```\n197: \n198: ### Error Response Format\n199: \n200: ```go\n201: type ErrorResponse struct {\n202:     Error       string `json:\"error\"`\n203:     Code        string `json:\"code\"`\n204:     RouteName   string `json:\"routeName,omitempty\"`\n205:     Timestamp   string `json:\"timestamp\"`\n206: }\n207: ```\n208: \n209: ### HTTP Status Codes\n210: \n211: | Scenario | Status Code |\n212: |----------|-------------|\n213: | Route not found | 404 |\n214: | Invalid resource type | 400 |\n215: | Malformed path | 400 |\n216: | Backend unavailable | 502 |\n217: | No healthy backends | 503 |\n218: | Backend timeout | 504 |\n219: \n220: ### Retry Strategy\n221: \n222: - **Connection errors**: Retry with next healthy backend (max 2 retries)\n223: - **Timeout**: Mark backend unhealthy, return 504\n224: - **Permanent errors** (4xx from backend): Return immediately\n225: \n226: ### Health Check Failure Policy\n227: \n228: ```\n229: Consecutive Failures → Action\n230: 3                   → Mark unhealthy, remove from rotation\n231: 1                   → Continue serving, log warning\n232: Recovery (1 success) → Mark healthy, restore to rotation\n233: ```\n234: \n235: ## Testing Strategy\n236: \n237: ### Unit Tests\n238: \n239: **File**: `router/router_test.go`\n240: \n241: ```go\n242: // Test cases:\n243: func TestRouter_Start(t *testing.T)\n244: func TestRouter_Shutdown(t *testing.T)\n245: func TestRouter_ServeHTTP(t *testing.T)\n246: func TestRouter_routeKey(t *testing.T)\n247: ```\n248: \n249: **File**: `router/resolver_test.go`\n250: \n251: ```go\n252: // Test cases:\n253: func TestResolver_ResolveRoute_Success(t *testing.T)\n254: func TestResolver_ResolveRoute_NotFound(t *testing.T)\n255: func TestResolver_ResolveRoute_Unhealthy(t *testing.T)\n256: func TestResolver_ParsePath(t *testing.T)\n257: ```\n258: \n259: **File**: `router/health_test.go`\n260: \n261: ```go\n262: // Test cases:\n263: func TestHealthChecker_CheckHealth_Success(t *testing.T)\n264: func TestHealthChecker_CheckHealth_Failure(t *testing.T)\n265: func TestHealthChecker_MarkUnhealthy(t *testing.T)\n266: func TestHealthChecker_MarkHealthy(t *testing.T)\n267: ```\n268: \n269: **File**: `router/handler_test.go`\n270: \n271: ```go\n272: // Test cases:\n273: func TestHandler_ProxyRequest_Success(t *testing.T)\n274: func TestHandler_ProxyRequest_BackendError(t *testing.T)\n275: func TestHandler_ProxyRequest_Timeout(t *testing.T)\n276: func TestHandler_AddForwardingHeaders(t *testing.T)\n277: ```\n278: \n279: ### Test Fixtures\n280: \n281: ```go\n282: func newTestRouteEntry(name, namespace, backendURL string) *RouteEntry {\n283:     return &RouteEntry{\n284:         Name:       name,\n285:         Namespace:  namespace,\n286:         Kind:       \"AgentRuntime\",\n287:         BackendURL: backendURL,\n288:         Health:     HealthStatus{Healthy: true},\n289:         UpdatedAt:  time.Now(),\n290:     }\n291: }\n292: \n293: func newTestRouterConfig() *RouterConfig {\n294:     return &RouterConfig{\n295:         ListenAddr:          \":8080\",\n296:         ReadTimeout:         15 * time.Second,\n297:         WriteTimeout:        30 * time.Second,\n298:         IdleTimeout:         60 * time.Second,\n299:         HealthCheckInterval: 10 * time.Second,\n300:         HealthCheckTimeout:  5 * time.Second,\n301:         UnhealthyThreshold:  3,\n302:     }\n303: }\n304: ```\n305: \n306: ### Mock Setup\n307: \n308: ```go\n309: // Fake kube client for testing\n310: func newFakeKubeClient(objects ...runtime.Object) *versioned.Clientset {\n311:     return fake.NewSimpleClientset(objects...)\n312: }\n313: \n314: // Mock backend server\n315: func newMockBackend(handler http.HandlerFunc) *httptest.Server {\n316:     return httptest.NewServer(handler)\n317: }\n318: ```\n319: \n320: ### Integration Tests\n321: \n322: **File**: `router/router_integration_test.go`\n323: \n324: ```go\n325: // Test scenarios (requires kind cluster):\n326: // 1. CRD creation triggers route addition\n327: // 2. CRD deletion triggers route removal\n328: // 3. End-to-end request routing\n329: // 4. Health check removes unhealthy backend\n330: // 5. Concurrent request handling\n331: ```\n332: \n333: ### Coverage Requirements\n334: \n335: - Route resolution: 100%\n336: - Proxy handler: 100%\n337: - Health check: 100%\n338: - Error handling paths: 100%\n339: - Overall: ≥85%\n340: \n341: ## Implementation Notes\n342: \n343: ### Route Key Format\n344: \n345: Routes stored in sync.Map with key: `{namespace}/{kind}/{name}`\n346: - Kind is lowercased: `agentruntime` or `codeinterpreter`\n347: \n348: ### Labels Monitored\n349: \n350: Informer filters resources with labels:\n351: - `agentcube.volcano.sh/expose: \"true\"` (only exposed resources are routed)\n352: \n353: ### Backend URL Discovery\n354: \n355: Backend URL extracted from CR spec:\n356: - AgentRuntime: `.spec.endpoint`\n357: - CodeInterpreter: `.spec.serviceURL`\n358: \n359: ### Connection Pooling\n360: \n361: HTTP client configured with:\n362: ```go\n363: &http.Transport{\n364:     MaxConnsPerHost:     config.MaxConnsPerHost,\n365:     MaxIdleConns:        100,\n366:     MaxIdleConnsPerHost: 10,\n367:     IdleConnTimeout:     90 * time.Second,\n368: }\n369: ```\n370: \n371: ### Graceful Shutdown\n372: \n373: 1. Stop accepting new connections\n374: 2. Close idle connections\n375: 3. Wait for in-flight requests (max 30s)\n376: 4. Stop informers\n377: 5. Close Kubernetes client\n\n(End of file - total 377 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Design: AR-009 Router HTTP Reverse Proxy Core\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation for the Router module (`pkg/router`) that acts as an HTTP reverse proxy, routing incoming requests to appropriate AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter backends based on Kubernetes CRD resources.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Structure\n\n```\npkg/router/\n├── router.go                   # Main router implementation\n├── router_test.go             # Unit tests\n├── handler.go                 # HTTP handler for proxy requests\n├── handler_test.go            # Handler tests\n├── resolver.go                # Route resolution logic\n├── resolver_test.go           # Resolver tests\n├── health.go                  # Health check manager\n├── health_test.go             # Health check tests","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/router/design.md","time":{"start":1775848541725,"end":1775848541733}}}}
